text: Olga Efimova (born 6 January 1990) is a Russian volleyball player, who plays as an outside hitter. She is a member of the Russia women's national volleyball team and participated at the 2015 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Cup in Japan. At club level she played for VC Zarechie Odintsovo in 2015. ==References== ==External links== *FIVB profile *Profile at CEV * Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:Russian women's volleyball players
